107
00:04:39,660 --> 00:04:41,059
though at that time I had not set up

108
00:04:41,059 --> 00:04:42,179
the doors upon the gates,

109
00:04:42,179 --> 00:04:44,899
notice verse two, that Sanballat and Geshem

110
00:04:44,899 --> 00:04:46,700
sent unto me saying,

111
00:04:46,700 --> 00:04:50,579
come, let us meet together in some one of the villages

112
00:04:50,579 --> 00:04:52,700
in the plain of Ono.

113
00:04:52,700 --> 00:04:57,019
But they thought to do me mischief.

114
00:04:57,019 --> 00:04:58,179
If you've already looked at the back

115
00:04:58,179 --> 00:05:00,059
of the bulletin this morning,

116
00:05:00,059 --> 00:05:03,100
the title is found here in verse number two

117
00:05:03,100 --> 00:05:04,980
for our message this morning.

118
00:05:04,980 --> 00:05:09,299
They thought to do me mischief.

119
00:05:09,299 --> 00:05:13,940
That word mischief is often translated as evil.

120
00:05:13,940 --> 00:05:16,980
Not that mischief is a wrong translation of the word,

121
00:05:16,980 --> 00:05:17,980
but it's synonymous,

122
00:05:17,980 --> 00:05:21,700
and we understand that it's translated various ways,

123
00:05:21,700 --> 00:05:24,420
but the mischief that was intended to be done

124
00:05:24,420 --> 00:05:26,700
against Nehemiah and those that were doing the work,

125
00:05:26,700 --> 00:05:31,100
they had evil intentions against the man of God

126
00:05:31,100 --> 00:05:32,660
